    "text": "Yeah, I think to your point Good point, Councilmember. We will actually talk about what is probably more commonplace as you might think about revenue bonds in the next presentation. And so we will have one more after this where I think we will get to even a more definitive sort of differential. The public facility revenue bonds, the revenues there are really just the general revenues of the city. It is not the revenues of, for instance, in our next presentation we will talk about the revenues of the sewer fund. Those are finite, distinct set of revenues that are accounted for separately. Those are pledged to the repayment of the bonds in the sewer. What we're talking about with this public facility revenue, the revenues there is really the general revenues of the city. It's not one specific line item."
