    "speaker": "Unknown (AB)",
    "speaker_source": "unresolved",
    "speaker_source_detail": "AssemblyAI could not identify speaker",
    "start": 13382018.0,
    "end": 13411001.0,
    "text": "I think what we're saying is that we want to do enough work so we could show something, right, like a concept or an area, because, you know, it's very difficult to get feedback when you have nothing to show. The public. So it would be very preliminary, more concept-related on how wide it's going to be and what trees would be impacted. It would be to that level, whereas rather than going in with nothing at all and saying, hey, we're doing a project here—"
